--长春大学的副教授，2024年11月发布的，
-- Prof. Dr. Jian Zhao 长春大学的教授

---------------------------------------------
好的，以下是一个更为详细且丰富的邮件和推荐信草稿，您可以根据需求发送给引用您文章的学者，并提供中文版。

---

### 邮件主题：
Request for Recommendation Letter in Support of My NIW Application

---

### 邮件正文：

Dear Dr./Professor [对方姓名],

I hope this message finds you well. My name is **[您的全名]**, and I am currently a [您的职位，例如 "PhD student" 或 "researcher"] at [您的单位名称]. I recently noticed that you cited my paper titled **"[A]"** in your work, "[B]," particularly the section on fragment sampling, which has greatly contributed to the success of your model. I truly appreciate your recognition and am grateful for the academic connection we share.

As part of my application for the **National Interest Waiver (NIW)** in the United States, I am required to submit several recommendation letters from experts who can speak to the significance of my research and its impact. Given your citation of my work and your application of the methods I proposed, I would be deeply honored if you could provide a recommendation letter to support my application.

To make the process easier for you, I have drafted a recommendation letter below that summarizes the contributions of my research, specifically related to your work. If you find the content suitable, I would greatly appreciate it if you could review it and, if it meets your approval, kindly sign it. Of course, if you would like to suggest any revisions or need additional information, I am more than happy to provide it.

Your recommendation would be a tremendous support in my NIW application, as your work in this field, along with your understanding of the significance of my research, will add great weight to the application.

Thank you very much for considering my request. Please let me know if you need further details about my research or the NIW application process.

Looking forward to hearing from you soon.

Best regards,  
[您的全名]  
[您的职务]  
[您的单位名称]  
[您的电子邮件]  
[您的联系电话]

---

### 附件：推荐信草稿

**推荐信草稿**

To Whom It May Concern,

I am writing this letter in support of **[您的全名]**’s application for the **National Interest Waiver (NIW)**. I have had the privilege of incorporating **[您的全名]**'s research into my own work, which I published in the paper titled **"[B]"**. In particular, I have applied his innovative method for fragment sampling, specifically the 50% overlapping sampling technique of EEG data for feature extraction. This technique, as described in his paper **"[A]"**, has proven to be an invaluable contribution to our model, significantly improving the accuracy and efficiency of our results.

The work of **[您的全名]** has made a notable impact in the field of **[您的研究领域，例如 "epileptic seizure prediction" or "neuroengineering" ]**, particularly in the context of analyzing **EEG signals**. His innovative approach to **[例如“real-time prediction of epileptic seizures” or "improving signal processing techniques"]** has significantly advanced the field by offering more precise methods for data interpretation and prediction. This is particularly crucial in the clinical applications of his research, which have the potential to reduce healthcare costs and improve patient outcomes.

**[您的全名]**'s research aligns perfectly with U.S. national interests in the areas of **[例如 "biomedical technologies," "public health," "neurological disorders," or "healthcare innovation"]**, and I am confident that his continued work will contribute to the advancement of these fields. His efforts to improve prediction systems for neurological conditions such as epilepsy, stroke, and heart arrhythmias are groundbreaking, and his potential for future research is immense.

In summary, I highly recommend **[您的全名]** for the **National Interest Waiver (NIW)**. His research has already made significant contributions to the field, and I have no doubt that it will continue to benefit the U.S. in the areas of healthcare technology and public health. Should you require any further information, please do not hesitate to contact me.

Sincerely,  
[对方姓名]  
[对方职位]  
[对方单位名称]  
[对方联系电话]  
[对方电子邮件]

